title: Grateful Dead Live at Alpine Valley Music Theatre on 1987-06-26
lineage: Nakamichi CR7A>Lucid AD9624>Fostex D5>DAT> Tascam DA20MKII>Tascam CDRW700>CDR>Wavelab 6>CDWave>Flac Frontend(Level 6); Recording by DATBRAD; Master cassette transfer to DAT by Mark Lynn; DAT to CDR and conversion to wav>flac by DATBRAD
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger-> Franklin's Tower, Walkin' Blues, Row Jimmy, Tons Of Steel, When Push Comes To Shove, Cassidy, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Space-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> The Wheel-> Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text: Great run Glad to see a version of this show on here without all of the tape cuts during the Stranger.  The tape I had went to a party and someone hit the record button, cutting out some of the peaks of the jam, just like the other version that was up here.  I recall feeling like a ping-pong ball bouncing around with some of the string of notes Jerry assembled. My rating is biased; it was a great run of shows at Alpine; great venue, great intensity, great crowd, great energy.  Not getting arrested by the Wisconsin State troopers on the way into the lot was a bonus too.  Thanks for uploading!
- Not at all a good show, especially for 1987.

Alpine Dead Don't think this was a good show? Listen to the crowd during Know You Rider. It was a great show if you were there. It had a very light jazzy fast feel to it with lots of energy spilling over add all the clean tabs & water moving thru everyone and you've got Disneyland for all us Heads. The lot was Woodstock which in a few years later would turn into something completely different. There's lots of great shows on the West Coast during '87 but like one Head said to the other "Just had to be there"
